$title
Rich Text
$
Some of the text fields in JANOARG allows rich text to be used. Rich text allows text to change appearance 
or layout dynamically. JANOARG uses TextMesh Pro's rich text syntax, which uses a tag-like syntax similar to 
HTML or XML.

$t2
Overview

$
A simple tag is defined with a tag name and looks like this: 
$n
<indent=2em><b><tag></b>
$
<indent=0>Tags may have additional values or attributes, which follows the following syntax:
$n
<indent=2em><b><tag="value"></b> or <b><tag attribute="value"></b>
$
<indent=0>Tags only affect the portion of text that stands after it. Most tags can be closed with a 
closing tag (<b></tag></b>), which will limit the effect of the corresponding tag to the portion 
of the text behind it.

$t2
List of Tags
$
The list below lists the tags that work in JANOARG. JANOARG does not use all the tags used by TextMesh Pro.

$
 • <indent=2em><b><noparse><b></noparse></b>
$n
Makes the text bold, <b>like this.</b>

$
 • <indent=2em><b><noparse><i></noparse></b>
$n
Italicize the text, <i>like this.</i>

$
 • <indent=2em><b><noparse><u></noparse></b>
$n
Add an underline to the text, <u>like this.</u>

$
 • <indent=2em><b><noparse><color=[color]></noparse></b>
$n
Colors the text. [color] can be one of the defined keywords (
<color=black>black</color>, 
<color=blue>blue</color>, 
<color=green>green</color>, 
<color=orange>orange</color>, 
<color=purple>purple</color>, 
<color=red>red</color>, 
<color=white>white</color>, 
and <color=yellow>yellow</color>), 
or a 6 or 8 digit hexadecimal color (#RRGGBB / #RRGGBBAA).

$
 • <indent=2em><b><noparse><noparse></noparse></b>
$n
Disable tag parsing for the text, which would make text display text that would be interpreted as tags.
